The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Tuesday, August 10, 2004 				 Global Trust suffers Rs 812cr loss
 G. S. RADHAKRISHNA																								Hyderabad, Aug. 9: Global Trust Bank has suffered a net loss of Rs 812.38 crore for 2003-04 compared with Rs 272.70 crore in the previous year.																								The Global Trust board today took stock of the accounts against the backdrop of the proposed amalgamation with Oriental Bank of Commerce.																								The operating loss was only Rs 79 crore, a bank statement said. Another Rs 164 crore comprised accelerated and prudent provisioning of select items, including non-banking assets.																								The loss was also due to provisioning of Rs 535 crore towards the weakening securities of earlier non-performing assets (NPAs).																								The low-cost deposits  current and savings  posted a growth of 28.61 per cent and 30.75 per cent, respectively. Global Trusts share of retail deposits also grew 74 per cent. The growth was driven by acquisition of over 77,000 new retail customer accounts. 
